The paper deals with a problem of coordinating the movements of multiple computational entities (robots) in a given space, which is a common theme in multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). The problem involves the use of algorithms to ensure that the robots move without colliding, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of external visible lights on the robots, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
